</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucaithcaidh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caith Caidh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/8/02 11:47:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=137.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dragonfang vs. Lifebane</span><hr size=1> If an assassin is killing an even tank 100% of the time.. it's overpowered (Assuming the assassin get's the jump).  This may be an inf only issue, as I know I likely won't be able to manage weapon, stealth, AND envenom at 50 until fairly far in the future.  However, I don't think we should be at the mercy of any class that we get the jump on.  As is, there are certain classes that we really ought to be able to kill (Again, assuming our initial advantage) that we have no shot against.  I would give up any chance I had to kill a tank for a decent shot at killing an enemy healer.  Perhaps it's just my luck, but my realm (Hib) is the one realm whose primary healer does not have access to some form of instant cast crowd control.<br>
I would argue that our chances against anyone of even con that we get the jump on should be 50% at the least.  Given how tough it is to set up and get into position, how easy it is for you to lag out of an opener, or to miss the CD when the prey moves, how unlikely it is that you'll ever actually get a solo shot at an even con tank, with nobody to interfere...  I don't think it's a problem for us to get a decent number of those kills.<br>
If our targets are diversified, it also helps the common conception that we pick on mages.  Of course we do.  They're the only ones that we can both find, and kill.  Give us the ability to kill healers (Anything to stop that insta at least before the CD) and not only do we get more targets, but we become more important defensively, as our own realm's healers are also at risk, and need protection.  <br>
As for crits... They are so infrequent that it seems ridiculous (It amazes me how many people spell this word with the syllable &quot;red&quot;) to cut down on that lucky bonus.  I agree with Val that targeting them is a mistake, and will have next to no effect on the actual problem (SBs with really big weapons one-shotting).<br>
Also, bear in mind that what you describe as &quot;too powerful&quot; is a spec that only an infi has a chance at.  As our three classes are more closely linked than any others, please remember that a change you recommend to bring infiltrators into balance may very well be executed on the other two classes as well.  I don't regard either SBs or NSs as overly powerful.  Infis may well be (I've had some encounters with infis where I was left to simply gasp at the amount of damage their use-anytime styles seemed to be doing.  (This coming from a blades shade.  I know what the bonus against leather is like.  This was simply hittign really hard)).  I just really do not want to see us needing to climb out of another pit.  The one we were in for the first 4 months was deep enough, thank you. <p><IMG SRC="http://www.dopplex.net/sigfile2.jpg" ALT="Caith Caidh, 35th Season Nightshade, An Claidheamh Soluis" ALIGN="middle"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucamillorogue.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Camillo Rogue</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/9/02 1:24:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=137.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dragonfang vs. Lifebane</span><hr size=1> infil team lead guy.<br>
